Document: ConcavePolygonShape3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_concavepolygonshape3d.rst  
Summary: A 3D trimesh shape for physics, used with CollisionShape3D nodes, offering high configurability but with performance and usage limitations.  

A 3D trimesh shape intended for use in physics, typically paired with CollisionShape3D nodes. As a collection of interconnected triangles, ConcavePolygonShape3D allows creation of polyhedra of any type, including non-enclosing volumes. However, it remains hollow even when triangles form a closed volume, making it unsuitable for many physics applications.  

Note: Intended for static CollisionShape3D nodes like StaticBody3D; may not work well with CharacterBody3D or RigidBody3D in non-Static modes.  
Warning: Small physics bodies moving quickly may clip through this shape due to its hollow nature, failing to detect collisions between frames.  
Performance: Slowest 3D collision shape due to complexity; optimal for level geometry. For convex shapes, use ConvexPolygonShape3D. For dynamic concave collision, use multiple ConvexPolygonShape3D instances via convex decomposition.
---CHUNK---
