Document: ConcavePolygonShape3D
Path: godot/classes/class_concavepolygonshape3d.rst
Summary: Configures backface collision behavior for concave polygon shapes and related methods.

Property: backface_collision (bool) = false
Controls whether collisions occur on both sides of concave shape faces. When true, collisions are detected on both sides; when false, collisions only occur along face normals.

Method: set_backface_collision_enabled(value: bool) → void
Enables or disables backface collision detection by setting the value parameter.

Method: is_backface_collision_enabled() → bool
Returns the current state of backface collision detection (true if enabled, false if disabled).
---CHUNK---
Document: ConcavePolygonShape3D
Path: godot/classes/class_concavepolygonshape3d.rst
Summary: Methods for retrieving and setting triangle face data in a 3D concave polygon shape.

Method: get_faces() → PackedVector3Array
Returns the faces of the trimesh shape as an array of vertices. The array (of length divisible by three) is naturally divided into triples; each triple of vertices defines a triangle.

Method: set_faces(faces: PackedVector3Array)
Sets the faces of the trimesh shape from an array of vertices. The faces array should be composed of triples such that each triple of vertices defines a triangle.